  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ELECTRICAL SUPERINTENDENT",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Supervise/ perform fault diagnosis, trouble shooting, maintenance, servicing and installation of electrical system/ component in workshops and onboard vessels.</li><li>Lead, directs and supervise a team of engineers in preparation of commissioning of ship board Machinery System/ Electrical & Automation System and Equipment, ensuring the completion on schedule in accordance to the protocols</li><li>Manage resources planning and provide technical advice</li><li>Liaise with various departments within the company and client to expedite the scope of work</li><li>Coordinate with vendors and partners, conduct design reviews with customers, and maintain documentation according to our ISO quality systems</li><li>Conduct in-depth troubleshooting of electrical connections and programmable Logic Controllers (PLC) Programs</li><li>Conduct risk assessment of electrical work on-site</li><li>Prepare work completion repots for Customer’s Acceptance</li><li>Identify opportunities for process improvement and work productivity</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Diploma/ Relevant Technical Qualification in electrical Engineering or equivalent</li><li>At least 5 years’ relevant experience in Marine related or oil & Gas industry</li><li>Experienced dealing with 440v Main Switchboard, Distribution Boards, Transformer, Power Generator, Main Engine, Converter, Inverter Batteries, Fire Alarm & Flooding System and Ship Control Monitoring & Management System</li></ul>",
